CRC Card 1 — Aircraft

Responsibilities
Hold current aircraft state (flight number, type, position, altitude, etc.)
Update its state when new data arrives
Provide its current details when requested

Collaborators
AircraftRepository
DangerDetector
ATCDisplay

CRC Card 2 — TransponderReceiver

Responsibilities
Receive incoming transponder data packets
Parse packets into aircraft updates (flight id + new state)
Send updates to the repository

Collaborators
AircraftRepository

CRC Card 3 — AircraftRepository

Responsibilities
Store and manage Aircraft objects (create if new, update if existing)
Provide aircraft list for display
Provide one aircraft’s details for queries

Collaborators
Aircraft
ATCDisplay
ControllerConsole
DangerDetector

CRC Card 4 — ATCDisplay

Responsibilities
Show aircraft positions/info to the controller
Refresh display every 10 seconds using repository data
Allow selecting an aircraft on screen

Collaborators
AircraftRepository
ControllerConsole

CRC Card 5 — DangerDetector

Responsibilities
Analyze aircraft states for unsafe situations (e.g., too close, collision risk)
Generate alerts when danger is detected

Collaborators
AircraftRepository
Aircraft
ControllerConsole


CRC Card 6 — ControllerConsole

Responsibilities
Handle controller queries (request aircraft details)
Present alerts to the controller
Show detailed info for a selected aircraft

Collaborators
AircraftRepository
ATCDisplay
DangerDetector